gomodel:SYNGO_4963  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1, S3: immunogold labeling of GPR151 and electron microscopy of the interpeduncular nucleus (IPN) of mouse brains showed synaptic localization of GPR151 mostly at the plasma membrane with a minor proportion of GPR151 observed at SVs and active zones.\n\nDistribution in n=50 synaptic terminals from 3 WT mice that contained an active zone; 74% of particles at plasma membrane, 5% at AZ, 10% at SV, 1% at DCV (remaining particles were classified as 'other').\n\nFig. S2a,b: The majority of GPR151-expressing neurons (70%) are cholinergic neurons.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Supplemental Figure S3 shows the schematic of the brain area dissected for EM (referring to mouse brain used in Figure 1). \"Representative micrographs of pre-embedding immunogold EM analyses showing\nGPR151 immunogold particles at habenular terminals of WT mice indicating synaptic ...\"\n\nSupplemental M&M: \"A combination of three different GPR151 antibodies (30\nug of rabbit polyclonal anti-GPR151 (Sigma, RRID:AB_10743863), 10 ug of goat\npolyclonal anti-GPR151 (Santa Cruz, RRID:AB_2113821) and 20 ul of mouse polyclonal\nanti-GPR151 (Sigma, RRID:AB_10608138) were coupled to 15 mg of beads per sample\nduring 24 hr at 37°C in 1.5 ml volume.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4963" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

